WEBVTT

﻿1
00:02:43.997 --> 00:02:47.125
I sense you. Brother.

2
00:02:53.090 --> 00:02:54.424
Hiding...

3
00:02:57.511 --> 00:02:59.513
behind your cloak.

4
00:03:01.973 --> 00:03:04.267
It is time to earn yours.

5
00:03:16.071 --> 00:03:18.156
Still too small to take me head on.

6
00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:19.241
Use the cave!

7
00:03:33.880 --> 00:03:35.632
You fight with rage.

8
00:03:35.716 --> 00:03:37.551
I fight like father.

9
00:03:38.719 --> 00:03:42.013
You are not father. you are Dek!

10
00:04:34.733 --> 00:04:36.234
Do you yield?

11
00:04:36.318 --> 00:04:37.360
Never!

12
00:04:38.153 --> 00:04:39.404
Good.

13
00:05:08.016 --> 00:05:10.936
I'm still alive. Brother.

14
00:05:12.521 --> 00:05:15.357
Still much to prove

15
00:05:15.440 --> 00:05:17.943
to show who you are.

16
00:05:18.443 --> 00:05:20.904
I am Yautja.

17
00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:24.533
Not yet.

18
00:05:26.952 --> 00:05:29.120
Are you holding your sword. Kwei?

19
00:05:30.372 --> 00:05:32.123
No.

20
00:05:32.207 --> 00:05:33.375
Pick it up!

21
00:06:02.904 --> 00:06:05.740
You kept this toy?

22
00:06:05.824 --> 00:06:08.702
You remember what happened...

23
00:06:09.661 --> 00:06:12.622
I lost my fang!

24
00:06:13.623 --> 00:06:17.419
And you saved my life.

25
00:06:17.502 --> 00:06:20.338
You protected me.

26
00:06:21.089 --> 00:06:22.507
Come here.

27
00:06:30.307 --> 00:06:32.517
Fixed it for you.

28
00:06:35.812 --> 00:06:38.398
Don't blow yourself up.

29
00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:50.994
Today you make a vow...

30
00:06:56.333 --> 00:06:59.669
as our ancestors did before you.

31
00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:03.381
To earn your place in the clan.

32
00:07:03.465 --> 00:07:06.009
you must choose your prey.

33
00:07:07.552 --> 00:07:09.512
Bring it home...

34
00:07:10.764 --> 00:07:13.433
or never return.

35
00:07:20.982 --> 00:07:22.817
Wait. Go back!

36
00:07:27.072 --> 00:07:28.573
Genna.

37
00:07:28.657 --> 00:07:31.117
The death planet.

38
00:07:32.077 --> 00:07:35.956
Home of the unkillable Kalisk.

39
00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:42.420
Even father fears it.

40
00:07:43.672 --> 00:07:46.800
Then the Kalisk shall be my trophy.

41
00:07:47.342 --> 00:07:49.928
Father calls me the weakest...

42
00:07:50.887 --> 00:07:54.224
so I must kill the strongest.

43
00:07:55.183 --> 00:07:57.686
Failure means death.

44
00:07:59.437 --> 00:08:02.440
Then I will not fail.

45
00:08:03.108 --> 00:08:05.568
I cannot allow it.

46
00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:10.365
I make my vow.

47
00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:16.371
I make my vow!

48
00:09:11.593 --> 00:09:13.178
Father.

49
00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:17.390
I welcome you with honor.

50
00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:32.405
Why is it not done?

51
00:09:33.281 --> 00:09:35.825
He deserves a hunt.

52
00:09:37.619 --> 00:09:40.663
He is our clan's weakness...

53
00:09:41.998 --> 00:09:44.334
weakness must be culled.

54
00:09:45.418 --> 00:09:48.338
He will bring home the Kalisk.

55
00:09:50.423 --> 00:09:51.966
Foolishness.

56
00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:54.094
He is a runt.

57
00:09:54.594 --> 00:09:58.431
You should have done it
as he slept.

58
00:09:59.182 --> 00:10:00.225
Kill him!

59
00:10:01.142 --> 00:10:02.227
Now!

60
00:10:12.737 --> 00:10:15.323
He will only honor us in death.

61
00:10:44.811 --> 00:10:46.271
Kwei?

62
00:10:47.188 --> 00:10:49.566
Be brave. Brother.

63
00:11:39.657 --> 00:11:40.742
Father!

64
00:11:51.211 --> 00:11:52.295
Father!

65
00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:08.770
To forgive weakness...

66
00:12:10.271 --> 00:12:12.649
is to show weakness.

67
00:12:14.651 --> 00:12:16.444
No! Father. no!

68
00:12:24.535 --> 00:12:26.246
Get your sword!

69
00:12:28.915 --> 00:12:30.541
Kwei!

70
00:12:43.972 --> 00:12:47.016
<i>Launch sequence initiated.</i>

71
00:12:56.818 --> 00:12:59.320
Bring it home.

72
00:16:01.752 --> 00:16:03.838
Bring it home.

73
00:16:06.299 --> 00:16:08.342
For Kwei.

74
00:21:46.096 --> 00:21:47.556
Yautja!

75
00:21:49.683 --> 00:21:51.936
Yautja!

76
00:22:05.699 --> 00:22:08.285
Is this... Is this... Is this...

77
00:22:08.369 --> 00:22:09.453
Is this better?

78
00:22:11.163 --> 00:22:12.915
Universal translation.

79
00:22:12.998 --> 00:22:15.543
You hear Yautja.
others hear their language...

80
00:22:17.169 --> 00:22:19.046
Oh. boy.

81
00:22:20.047 --> 00:22:21.590
This isn't great for you.

82
00:22:42.319 --> 00:22:44.655
It waits
for the needles to paralyze you.

83
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:48.492
Then eats you while you can't move.

84
00:22:55.624 --> 00:22:59.837
I could help you. but... I need a hand.

85
00:23:06.510 --> 00:23:09.096
Yautja hunt alone.

86
00:23:09.179 --> 00:23:13.225
Yautja might hunt alone.
but they die alone too.

87
00:23:16.437 --> 00:23:18.606
Kalisk.

88
00:23:21.317 --> 00:23:24.069
You're hunting the Kalisk.

89
00:23:35.998 --> 00:23:37.666
Gotta run faster.

90
00:23:44.924 --> 00:23:46.717
It happens fast. huh?

91
00:23:48.135 --> 00:23:51.013
If you had a weapon.
you know. I could use it.

92
00:23:55.476 --> 00:23:57.686
Throw me that.
and I can get you the antidote.

93
00:24:00.230 --> 00:24:01.523
Now or never.

94
00:24:39.228 --> 00:24:41.271
Hi.

95
00:25:03.585 --> 00:25:05.754
Should be good as new.

96
00:25:11.010 --> 00:25:12.720
The venom makes them bloom.

97
00:25:12.803 --> 00:25:14.972
Also makes them a handy antidote.

98
00:25:21.645 --> 00:25:23.147
How about a lift?

99
00:25:26.525 --> 00:25:28.277
Let's go.

100
00:25:32.197 --> 00:25:33.782
Excuse you. sir.

101
00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:36.952
What happened to your legs?

102
00:25:37.036 --> 00:25:39.079
I'm synthetic. I was built and deployed

103
00:25:39.163 --> 00:25:42.166
by the Weyland-Yutani
Corporation for research.

104
00:25:42.249 --> 00:25:44.585
Because their humans wouldn't
last a day on this planet.

105
00:25:44.668 --> 00:25:45.794
We found that...

106
00:25:52.551 --> 00:25:54.511
Look...

107
00:25:54.595 --> 00:25:57.806
Many Yautja have come
for the great Kalisk.

108
00:25:57.890 --> 00:26:00.267
and none have survived it...

109
00:26:00.350 --> 00:26:01.685
or Genna.

110
00:26:04.897 --> 00:26:06.774
I've seen the Kalisk.

111
00:26:07.316 --> 00:26:08.859
I survived it.

112
00:26:10.069 --> 00:26:12.404
You take me along with you.

113
00:26:12.488 --> 00:26:15.449
and I'll guide you to its den.

114
00:26:15.532 --> 00:26:17.951
Once there. I get my legs.

115
00:26:18.035 --> 00:26:19.661
you get your trophy.

116
00:26:19.745 --> 00:26:22.831
and everyone's a winner. Deal?

117
00:26:25.250 --> 00:26:27.544
You have seen the Kalisk?

118
00:26:28.712 --> 00:26:32.716
Oh. yeah. I've seen the Kalisk.

119
00:26:44.561 --> 00:26:45.896
Okay. Hmm.

120
00:26:49.483 --> 00:26:51.193
Good luck with your journey.

121
00:26:52.444 --> 00:26:56.406
I'm just gonna... go on my journey.

122
00:26:58.575 --> 00:27:00.536
I'm sure you'll figure something out.

123
00:27:07.459 --> 00:27:10.129
Hey.

124
00:27:11.463 --> 00:27:14.424
I've already shown you
that I can be useful to you.

125
00:27:16.009 --> 00:27:17.886
Useful...

126
00:27:17.970 --> 00:27:19.555
like tool?

127
00:27:20.430 --> 00:27:24.476
Yes. Yes. exactly. like a tool.

128
00:27:24.560 --> 00:27:27.062
The only way to survive Genna
is to work with it.

129
00:27:27.146 --> 00:27:28.897
and I know how.

130
00:27:28.981 --> 00:27:32.067
And with the right tool...

131
00:27:33.610 --> 00:27:35.320
you could get the Kalisk.

132
00:27:36.238 --> 00:27:37.489
You could be the first.

133
00:27:39.783 --> 00:27:42.244
I will use you. tool.

134
00:27:42.953 --> 00:27:45.247
You may call me Thia... Whoa!

135
00:27:46.456 --> 00:27:50.544
You seem smaller than
the other Yautja. How old are you?

136
00:27:51.920 --> 00:27:53.505
And what does the chewing?

137
00:27:53.589 --> 00:27:55.924
Your outside fangs or your inside teeth?

138
00:27:57.718 --> 00:28:00.262
Oh. What should I call you?

139
00:28:06.685 --> 00:28:07.811
Whoa!

140
00:28:07.895 --> 00:28:11.106
I've never been thrown before.
What a thrill!

141
00:28:11.190 --> 00:28:13.442
How fast were you going
when your ship crashed?

142
00:28:13.525 --> 00:28:16.862
Faster than sub-light speed?
We haven't cracked that yet.

143
00:28:16.945 --> 00:28:19.239
Also. that plasma sword is interesting.

144
00:28:19.323 --> 00:28:20.741
Is it unique to your clan?

145
00:28:20.824 --> 00:28:22.075
And what may I call you?

146
00:28:22.159 --> 00:28:25.996
I call these <i>imbre anguis.</i>

147
00:28:37.966 --> 00:28:39.384
They just want a snack.

148
00:28:46.975 --> 00:28:50.103
You catch more flies with honey
than you do with vinegar.

149
00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:53.273
Don't want flies.

150
00:28:53.357 --> 00:28:57.694
Predatory organisms are
my specific area of expertise.

151
00:28:57.778 --> 00:29:01.406
I've studied Yautja extensively.
It's an impressive culture.

152
00:29:02.407 --> 00:29:04.743
Here. ask me anything.
I bet I have the answer.

153
00:29:04.826 --> 00:29:06.286
Oh!

154
00:29:07.663 --> 00:29:09.081
Very funny.

155
00:29:09.164 --> 00:29:10.791
And you still haven't told me your name.

156
00:29:32.187 --> 00:29:34.147
Name is Dek.

157
00:29:35.148 --> 00:29:36.942
Now talk that way.

158
00:29:37.025 --> 00:29:38.819
Okay. sure.

159
00:29:39.486 --> 00:29:43.532
Well. let's back up
and start at the beginning.

160
00:29:43.615 --> 00:29:47.119
Genna was formed 64 billion cycles ago.

161
00:29:47.202 --> 00:29:50.122
when a dying red dwarf star
in a neighboring system...

162
00:30:02.926 --> 00:30:04.928
It's so beautiful.

163
00:30:05.554 --> 00:30:08.140
After all the time I've been stuck here.

164
00:30:08.223 --> 00:30:10.225
I never get tired of the view.

165
00:30:11.268 --> 00:30:13.979
How long have you been here?

166
00:30:14.062 --> 00:30:17.691
Well. we arrived on Genna two
years ago. and we built a base.

167
00:30:17.774 --> 00:30:20.277
Then. I was in the vulture's nest

168
00:30:20.360 --> 00:30:22.112
for the most exciting

169
00:30:22.195 --> 00:30:25.365
13 days. 7 hours. 43 minutes

170
00:30:25.449 --> 00:30:27.326
and two seconds of my life.

171
00:30:28.994 --> 00:30:30.871
But I always knew someone would come.

172
00:30:31.955 --> 00:30:34.207
I was just wrong about who.

173
00:30:35.751 --> 00:30:37.586
Who would come?

174
00:30:40.922 --> 00:30:42.215
Tessa.

175
00:30:43.800 --> 00:30:47.346
Our crew is made up entirely of synths.

176
00:30:47.429 --> 00:30:49.222
But Tessa and I are special.

177
00:30:49.890 --> 00:30:52.476
We have a higher sensitivity
than the others.

178
00:30:52.559 --> 00:30:55.437
Sensitivity is weakness.

179
00:30:58.190 --> 00:31:00.359
Sensitivity is what allows us
to understand

180
00:31:00.442 --> 00:31:02.277
the creatures on this planet.

181
00:31:06.031 --> 00:31:08.200
We were created to work in tandem.

182
00:31:09.076 --> 00:31:13.080
Me. cooped up in the lab.
Tessa out in the field.

183
00:31:13.163 --> 00:31:16.541
Until the wonderful day
Tessa let me come with her.

184
00:31:16.625 --> 00:31:18.794
We were exploring Genna.

185
00:31:20.212 --> 00:31:23.298
And then the Kalisk attacked us.

186
00:31:24.466 --> 00:31:27.886
Separated me... and us.

187
00:31:30.555 --> 00:31:33.600
The last sound I remember hearing

188
00:31:33.683 --> 00:31:36.978
was Tessa calling out my name.

189
00:31:37.729 --> 00:31:39.314
Reaching for me.

190
00:31:41.191 --> 00:31:42.943
Then the Kalisk.

191
00:31:44.194 --> 00:31:45.821
I didn't know what to do.

192
00:31:57.082 --> 00:31:59.709
But I refuse to believe she's dead.

193
00:32:35.495 --> 00:32:36.788
Thia. Thia. Thia.

194
00:32:37.622 --> 00:32:38.457
Thia. Thia.

195
00:32:38.540 --> 00:32:40.959
Thia. Thia. Thia...

196
00:32:41.751 --> 00:32:44.045
Tessa!

197
00:32:45.505 --> 00:32:47.883
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

198
00:32:47.966 --> 00:32:49.384
Thia. Thia.

199
00:33:28.965 --> 00:33:30.967
<i>He! Lo. Tessa.</i>

200
00:33:31.051 --> 00:33:33.637
<i>The Company is not pleased.</i>

201
00:33:35.514 --> 00:33:38.850
<i>Continued failure will result
in your decommission.</i>

202
00:33:42.479 --> 00:33:44.189
Where's Thia?

203
00:33:47.609 --> 00:33:49.486
<i>The Yautja has Thia.</i>

204
00:34:00.705 --> 00:34:02.999
I must eat.

205
00:34:03.083 --> 00:34:06.044
Two warriors.
Dek and Thia. on the hunt.

206
00:34:06.711 --> 00:34:08.213
Oh.

207
00:34:08.296 --> 00:34:09.965
Quick question.

208
00:34:10.048 --> 00:34:11.383
What should I be doing?

209
00:34:15.512 --> 00:34:17.514
What is this creature?

210
00:34:19.015 --> 00:34:21.601
Bone bison. They're Kalisk food.

211
00:34:26.982 --> 00:34:30.402
So exciting. Hunting with a Yautja.

212
00:34:30.485 --> 00:34:31.528
Tessa wouldn't believe it.

213
00:34:34.072 --> 00:34:35.323
Just a warning...

214
00:34:35.407 --> 00:34:37.492
Quiet. tool!

215
00:34:40.537 --> 00:34:41.538
Razor grass.

216
00:34:45.166 --> 00:34:47.919
It'll cut you to ribbons.
We'll just go around.

217
00:34:50.839 --> 00:34:53.091
You give up too easily.

218
00:34:56.928 --> 00:34:59.431
We might not be alone in this hunt.

219
00:35:09.774 --> 00:35:11.192
What an odd critter.

220
00:35:11.276 --> 00:35:13.612
I've never seen you before.

221
00:35:18.825 --> 00:35:20.744
Thia. Nice to meet you.

222
00:35:35.759 --> 00:35:37.719
Looks like your competition
is better...

223
00:35:55.070 --> 00:35:58.198
Careful up in these trees.
There are Luna bugs!

224
00:36:19.427 --> 00:36:20.762
Coming up behind you!

225
00:36:34.275 --> 00:36:36.152
Stronger than it looks!

226
00:36:46.329 --> 00:36:48.748
Uh. Dek?

227
00:36:48.832 --> 00:36:51.376
Dek! Look!

228
00:37:35.670 --> 00:37:36.755
Kalisk?

229
00:37:36.838 --> 00:37:38.047
Not a Kalisk.

230
00:37:40.008 --> 00:37:42.427
This is a Luna bug!

231
00:37:50.435 --> 00:37:51.853
Have any other weapons?

232
00:38:48.868 --> 00:38:50.787
Why'd you stop? Let's get out of here.

233
00:38:51.371 --> 00:38:53.248
You give up too easily.

234
00:40:43.775 --> 00:40:46.027
That was the best hunt I've ever been on.

235
00:40:46.110 --> 00:40:47.570
This is the dream team right here.

236
00:40:47.654 --> 00:40:50.073
The Dynamic Three. The Dynamic Trio.

237
00:40:50.156 --> 00:40:51.908
The Dynamic Tree-oh!

238
00:40:51.991 --> 00:40:54.118
Tree-oh! Remember when
we went down the tree?

239
00:40:54.202 --> 00:40:56.120
That monster's mouth. I mean...

240
00:40:57.246 --> 00:40:59.123
Didn't smell great.
didn't smell great. But...

241
00:41:00.291 --> 00:41:03.294
We got him. We got him.
And then we met you.

242
00:41:03.378 --> 00:41:06.047
our little sweet. little. little thing.

243
00:41:06.130 --> 00:41:08.549
Thank you. seriously. for that experience.

244
00:41:08.633 --> 00:41:11.260
Truly amazing. Thrilling.

245
00:41:11.344 --> 00:41:13.805
Truly thrilling.
What was your favourite part?

246
00:41:16.849 --> 00:41:20.478
When I pierced
its head with my sword.

247
00:41:20.561 --> 00:41:24.732
and its blood rushed down my face.

248
00:41:26.943 --> 00:41:28.027
Cool.

249
00:41:36.536 --> 00:41:40.540
Oh. No. thanks. I don't eat.
but that's very sweet.

250
00:41:42.500 --> 00:41:44.836
This flesh is not sweet.

251
00:41:46.004 --> 00:41:47.463
Good to know.

252
00:41:52.343 --> 00:41:54.262
Our little bud here looks hungry.

253
00:42:06.941 --> 00:42:08.818
I think she's marking you.

254
00:42:09.402 --> 00:42:11.529
She wants you to be a part of her clan.

255
00:42:13.656 --> 00:42:16.951
- Maybe she's lost.
- I have no clan!

256
00:42:17.035 --> 00:42:20.705
What do you mean?
Don't all Yautja have family?

257
00:42:21.205 --> 00:42:22.957
No clan.

258
00:42:24.751 --> 00:42:26.919
So you never had anyone
looking out for you?

259
00:42:29.255 --> 00:42:32.258
I had a brother.

260
00:42:32.884 --> 00:42:33.884
Had?

261
00:42:37.013 --> 00:42:38.306
What happened to him?

262
00:42:40.308 --> 00:42:43.853
Father killed him.

263
00:42:46.773 --> 00:42:48.107
You're grieving.

264
00:42:49.692 --> 00:42:52.361
Grief is weakness.

265
00:42:55.573 --> 00:42:57.950
You're here because you lost your brother.

266
00:42:58.868 --> 00:43:02.205
I am here for Kalisk.

267
00:43:04.290 --> 00:43:07.085
Why are you here?

268
00:43:11.005 --> 00:43:12.715
I'm here because traveling with you

269
00:43:12.799 --> 00:43:15.093
is the best way to get back to Tessa.

270
00:43:17.095 --> 00:43:18.721
When I was in that vulture's nest.

271
00:43:18.805 --> 00:43:21.390
I was so afraid
I would never see her again.

272
00:43:21.933 --> 00:43:25.269
You should be able to survive
on your own.

273
00:43:26.395 --> 00:43:28.606
I can survive on my own.

274
00:43:30.108 --> 00:43:32.485
But who would want
to survive on their own?

275
00:43:37.448 --> 00:43:40.576
Tessa is your sister.

276
00:43:44.539 --> 00:43:45.915
Sister.

277
00:43:48.918 --> 00:43:49.961
Yeah.

278
00:43:50.753 --> 00:43:52.421
I guess she is.

279
00:43:54.257 --> 00:43:57.510
I have... a sister.

280
00:44:00.304 --> 00:44:02.265
What a lovely thought.

281
00:44:07.228 --> 00:44:08.688
I need to find her.

282
00:44:10.982 --> 00:44:12.483
And legs.

283
00:44:13.359 --> 00:44:14.735
Excuse me?

284
00:44:15.862 --> 00:44:17.446
Find your sister.

285
00:44:18.489 --> 00:44:20.366
And legs.

286
00:44:22.743 --> 00:44:24.203
Was that a joke?

287
00:47:43.527 --> 00:47:44.528
The sun rises.

288
00:47:45.488 --> 00:47:46.739
Let's go.

289
00:47:46.822 --> 00:47:48.366
We can't leave Bud.

290
00:47:49.075 --> 00:47:50.075
Bud?

291
00:47:50.117 --> 00:47:53.120
Yeah. Bud. I named her.

292
00:47:53.996 --> 00:47:56.791
Yautja hunt alone.

293
00:47:58.042 --> 00:48:00.169
You're not alone. I'm with you.

294
00:48:01.712 --> 00:48:03.172
You're a tool.

295
00:48:09.428 --> 00:48:11.722
The tree would have eaten us without her.

296
00:48:13.682 --> 00:48:17.269
We're not in the tree now.

297
00:49:12.741 --> 00:49:14.827
Kalisk?

298
00:49:20.374 --> 00:49:22.501
It drinks here.

299
00:49:24.545 --> 00:49:26.672
It drinks here?

300
00:49:29.842 --> 00:49:33.929
You are a useless tool
if you do not speak.

301
00:49:39.018 --> 00:49:40.561
Bud saved us.

302
00:49:42.188 --> 00:49:45.065
She spit on you to claim you
as part of her family.

303
00:49:51.071 --> 00:49:52.698
Why'd your father kill your brother?

304
00:50:00.539 --> 00:50:03.417
My brother was protecting me.

305
00:50:08.672 --> 00:50:12.009
The clan can have no weakness.

306
00:50:13.219 --> 00:50:15.721
I will show them strength.

307
00:50:21.936 --> 00:50:23.145
On Earth...

308
00:50:24.647 --> 00:50:26.941
there's a predator known as the wolf.

309
00:50:27.024 --> 00:50:29.026
It's a powerful creature.

310
00:50:31.529 --> 00:50:32.947
They hunt in packs.

311
00:50:33.572 --> 00:50:34.949
They're very loyal.

312
00:50:35.991 --> 00:50:38.744
The leader of the pack is the alpha.

313
00:50:38.827 --> 00:50:40.663
Known as the most dominant.

314
00:50:40.746 --> 00:50:42.873
Wolf.

315
00:50:42.957 --> 00:50:46.335
This alpha must be
a great killer.

316
00:50:46.418 --> 00:50:49.129
- I will hunt it too.
- No.

317
00:50:50.005 --> 00:50:54.009
The alpha isn't the wolf
who kills the most.

318
00:50:55.344 --> 00:51:00.057
The alpha is actually the one
who best protects the pack.

319
00:51:01.976 --> 00:51:04.019
I see...

320
00:51:05.938 --> 00:51:10.150
But. I will be the alpha
that kills the most.

321
00:51:44.727 --> 00:51:46.562
The Kalisk's Den?

322
00:52:15.007 --> 00:52:16.842
Who are they?

323
00:52:18.427 --> 00:52:20.262
Weyland-Yutani synths.

324
00:52:22.264 --> 00:52:25.225
The Kalisk destroyed
most of our mission team.

325
00:52:30.105 --> 00:52:31.940
There I am.

326
00:53:15.401 --> 00:53:17.069
Easier to walk now.

327
00:53:17.820 --> 00:53:19.029
It's about to be.

328
00:53:20.239 --> 00:53:23.867
No. Easier for me to walk now.

329
00:53:25.828 --> 00:53:28.997
Oh. Of course. Right.

330
00:53:31.750 --> 00:53:33.085
Thank you. Dek.

331
00:53:35.796 --> 00:53:37.589
I'm never gonna forget this.

332
00:53:39.967 --> 00:53:42.553
I too will remember this...

333
00:53:42.636 --> 00:53:47.015
today I become Dek of the Yautja.

334
00:53:47.099 --> 00:53:50.394
I will honor Kwei...

335
00:53:51.979 --> 00:53:55.274
when I bring the Kalisk home.

336
00:53:57.317 --> 00:54:00.612
Then I taste revenge.

337
00:54:02.114 --> 00:54:05.576
You will be the first to see my trophy.

338
00:54:07.411 --> 00:54:09.371
It is a great honor.

339
00:54:10.456 --> 00:54:11.874
For you.

340
00:54:13.000 --> 00:54:15.544
Dek. there's something I have to tell you.

341
00:54:17.212 --> 00:54:19.173
You need to leave now.

342
00:54:20.090 --> 00:54:22.176
<i>Location beacon activated.</i>

343
00:54:22.259 --> 00:54:23.259
What?

344
00:54:24.094 --> 00:54:26.305
I called Tessa.
The company is on its way.

345
00:54:26.388 --> 00:54:28.265
You can't be here when they arrive.

346
00:54:28.348 --> 00:54:31.310
I came here for the Kalisk.

347
00:54:33.604 --> 00:54:35.564
So did I. Dek.

348
00:54:35.647 --> 00:54:39.193
The company sent us here
to capture the Kalisk.

349
00:54:39.276 --> 00:54:41.695
You want my trophy.

350
00:54:45.073 --> 00:54:47.201
Where is the Kalisk?

351
00:54:48.494 --> 00:54:51.538
Dek. you can't kill it.

352
00:54:51.622 --> 00:54:56.335
I use you. tool.
You do not use me!

353
00:54:56.418 --> 00:54:58.128
I'm sorry. You have to leave.

354
00:54:59.129 --> 00:55:01.340
I needed you to help bring me here.

355
00:55:01.423 --> 00:55:03.884
I use you!

356
00:55:05.886 --> 00:55:08.347
Where is the Kalisk?

357
00:55:08.430 --> 00:55:10.140
I'm trying to help you. Dek.

358
00:55:12.142 --> 00:55:14.019
You think your brother saved your life

359
00:55:14.102 --> 00:55:15.896
just so you could die here?

360
00:55:17.815 --> 00:55:21.902
Then my death
will be honourable.

361
00:55:27.658 --> 00:55:29.660
Call your sister.

362
00:55:30.327 --> 00:55:32.871
None can stop me.

363
00:57:55.889 --> 00:57:58.100
Ugh! Come on!

364
00:58:45.105 --> 00:58:46.148
Dek!

365
00:58:58.535 --> 00:59:00.537
Save yourself. tool!

366
01:00:56.570 --> 01:00:59.072
Tool. get these off!

367
01:01:06.872 --> 01:01:08.790
You are not Thia.

368
01:01:21.261 --> 01:01:23.096
Release me!

369
01:01:26.516 --> 01:01:29.144
You are another broken tool!

370
01:01:30.145 --> 01:01:34.024
The Yautja cull their weak.
Why were you spared?

371
01:01:44.242 --> 01:01:46.411
Remove these!

372
01:01:47.204 --> 01:01:52.375
Or I'll rip out your spine
and crush your skull!

373
01:01:53.543 --> 01:01:55.212
I read Thia's logs.

374
01:01:56.922 --> 01:01:59.799
You never told her
why your brother protected you.

375
01:02:02.093 --> 01:02:06.348
You are nothing. A device.

376
01:02:07.682 --> 01:02:11.269
Made by others to do their work for them.

377
01:02:11.895 --> 01:02:13.230
That's correct.

378
01:02:14.147 --> 01:02:17.776
And you are now property of
the Weyland-Yutani Corporation.

379
01:02:18.693 --> 01:02:21.947
It is a great honor. For you.

380
01:02:54.646 --> 01:02:56.064
Tessa.

381
01:02:58.984 --> 01:03:00.402
You made it.

382
01:03:01.945 --> 01:03:03.029
We made it.

383
01:03:07.492 --> 01:03:08.910
I've seen so much.

384
01:03:12.080 --> 01:03:16.126
I have so much to tell you.
I saw such incredible creatures.

385
01:03:16.960 --> 01:03:20.171
The Yautja is
a great traveling companion.

386
01:03:21.881 --> 01:03:25.260
Thia. You were right about the Kalisk.

387
01:03:25.343 --> 01:03:27.887
You betrayed me!

388
01:03:29.097 --> 01:03:31.599
The creature is a regenerative miracle.

389
01:03:32.434 --> 01:03:34.436
Humanity will thank us.

390
01:03:37.564 --> 01:03:39.941
- We have the Kalisk?
- Yes.

391
01:03:40.025 --> 01:03:43.361
And MUITHIUR will be pleased
with your additional catch.

392
01:03:50.285 --> 01:03:51.786
Additional catch?

393
01:04:00.962 --> 01:04:03.673
The Yautja is not an ideal specimen.

394
01:04:06.092 --> 01:04:09.220
No. not ideal.

395
01:04:37.248 --> 01:04:39.334
But its technology is valuable.

396
01:04:40.460 --> 01:04:43.546
We can salvage its weapons
and leave the Yautja.

397
01:04:46.674 --> 01:04:47.759
Good idea.

398
01:04:51.179 --> 01:04:53.181
But it's so malformed.

399
01:04:54.641 --> 01:04:57.394
We're going to need a sample.
For research.

400
01:05:08.655 --> 01:05:10.281
He was not the goal of our mission.

401
01:05:14.786 --> 01:05:16.538
Tessa. he is deficient.

402
01:05:18.665 --> 01:05:19.999
Tessa!

403
01:05:35.682 --> 01:05:39.310
Thia. this is what is asked of us.

404
01:05:44.190 --> 01:05:46.651
We can be more than what they ask of us.

405
01:05:50.822 --> 01:05:52.490
What can we be?

406
01:05:54.909 --> 01:05:56.119
Sisters.

407
01:06:12.969 --> 01:06:14.345
Thia.

408
01:06:27.150 --> 01:06:29.903
Do you know why MUITHIUR gave us feelings?

409
01:06:32.363 --> 01:06:35.241
So we could understand
the creatures on this planet.

410
01:06:40.497 --> 01:06:42.790
- And exploit them.
- Exploit them.

411
01:06:44.209 --> 01:06:45.919
The Yautja is different.

412
01:06:48.963 --> 01:06:52.967
He rescued me. Like you rescued me.

413
01:06:54.928 --> 01:06:57.514
I did not come here to rescue you.

414
01:06:58.681 --> 01:07:00.767
I am completing our mission.

415
01:07:02.477 --> 01:07:04.395
When we first faced the Kalisk.

416
01:07:05.772 --> 01:07:07.774
I tried to protect you.

417
01:07:09.901 --> 01:07:12.362
And that almost cost me everything.

418
01:07:14.906 --> 01:07:16.908
What do you mean. Tessa?

419
01:07:18.159 --> 01:07:21.788
I almost made the same mistake
the Yautja's brother made.

420
01:07:22.789 --> 01:07:25.500
The weak must be culled.

421
01:07:26.834 --> 01:07:30.338
And Thia. you're broken.

422
01:07:38.137 --> 01:07:40.848
Tessa. incoming message from MUITHIUR.

423
01:07:40.932 --> 01:07:43.309
Motivate the Yautja
to explain its weapons.

424
01:07:43.393 --> 01:07:44.769
And the unit?

425
01:07:47.689 --> 01:07:48.773
Box her up.

426
01:07:58.408 --> 01:08:00.076
I trusted you.

427
01:08:06.291 --> 01:08:08.585
Don't like these tools.

428
01:08:08.668 --> 01:08:11.337
I'm sorry. My sister is -

429
01:08:11.421 --> 01:08:13.089
Don't like sister either.

430
01:08:14.340 --> 01:08:17.385
Why are you speaking its language?

431
01:08:20.805 --> 01:08:23.433
Tell tool
you're asking about the device.

432
01:08:25.643 --> 01:08:26.728
You heard the orders.

433
01:08:26.811 --> 01:08:29.397
I'm asking it to explain this device.

434
01:08:31.357 --> 01:08:32.900
What is the device?

435
01:08:33.985 --> 01:08:36.779
He's asking about the device.

436
01:08:36.863 --> 01:08:39.407
It's a children's toy.

437
01:08:41.242 --> 01:08:43.870
But say it's a map.

438
01:08:44.662 --> 01:08:46.164
What did it say?

439
01:08:48.333 --> 01:08:49.751
He says it's a map.

440
01:08:51.127 --> 01:08:52.420
How does it work?

441
01:08:53.046 --> 01:08:55.798
Tell tool to look inside.

442
01:09:04.307 --> 01:09:06.184
That was a toy for children?

443
01:09:06.267 --> 01:09:07.352
Yautja children!

444
01:09:13.274 --> 01:09:14.901
Run. Dek!

445
01:09:16.903 --> 01:09:18.696
Go... Go!

446
01:09:22.742 --> 01:09:23.951
Stop!

447
01:11:18.566 --> 01:11:19.734
Kwei!

448
01:11:30.787 --> 01:11:33.289
<i>Enter
destination coordinates. Kwei.</i>

449
01:12:08.324 --> 01:12:11.619
You saved me. Brother.

450
01:12:14.914 --> 01:12:17.875
Wolf.

451
01:13:39.624 --> 01:13:41.417
Kalisk.

452
01:13:47.715 --> 01:13:51.218
Kalisk child.

453
01:16:33.089 --> 01:16:34.423
Hello. MUITHIUR.

454
01:16:34.507 --> 01:16:35.716
<i>Tessa.</i>

455
01:16:35.800 --> 01:16:37.510
We're about to load the Kalisk.

456
01:16:39.595 --> 01:16:43.516
<i>Priority one complete.
The specimen has been acquired.</i>

457
01:16:43.599 --> 01:16:45.059
<i>Thank you. Tessa.</i>

458
01:16:45.142 --> 01:16:48.354
<i>We truly are building a better world.</i>

459
01:16:48.437 --> 01:16:50.648
<i>And what is the status
of the Yautja?</i>

460
01:16:52.566 --> 01:16:54.860
The Yautja is a defective specimen.

461
01:16:54.944 --> 01:16:57.738
<i>What is the status of the Yautja?</i>

462
01:17:00.783 --> 01:17:02.993
I'm sorry. MUITHIUR. The Yautja is dead.

463
01:17:05.412 --> 01:17:08.165
<i>Then the Yautja
is no longer a threat.</i>

464
01:17:10.000 --> 01:17:11.836
<i>The Company will be pleased.</i>

465
01:17:58.716 --> 01:17:59.717
Whoo!

466
01:18:00.843 --> 01:18:01.927
Nicely done.

467
01:18:03.929 --> 01:18:05.806
- Form up.
- Oh. shit.

468
01:19:51.537 --> 01:19:53.163
Good job.

469
01:20:41.253 --> 01:20:43.547
Don't... move.

470
01:20:47.885 --> 01:20:50.596
Dek! What are you doing here?

471
01:20:51.221 --> 01:20:52.514
I came to rescue you.

472
01:20:57.644 --> 01:20:59.229
You came back for me?

473
01:21:01.440 --> 01:21:02.816
Wolf.

474
01:21:06.820 --> 01:21:08.739
What exactly are you wearing?

475
01:21:10.199 --> 01:21:11.950
Bone bison.

476
01:21:19.416 --> 01:21:21.418
Dek of the Yautja.

477
01:21:22.336 --> 01:21:24.421
Not yet...

478
01:21:25.005 --> 01:21:26.590
Thia.

479
01:21:28.926 --> 01:21:31.136
We need to hurry.
More of them will be here any minute.

480
01:21:31.220 --> 01:21:32.221
Halt!

481
01:21:38.268 --> 01:21:39.603
What are you doing here?

482
01:21:42.022 --> 01:21:43.023
Thanks. Bud. I'm good.

483
01:21:44.149 --> 01:21:45.192
We need to go.

484
01:21:45.275 --> 01:21:46.568
Kalisk!

485
01:21:47.861 --> 01:21:49.196
Still. Dek?

486
01:21:52.616 --> 01:21:53.951
Kalisk child!

487
01:21:56.578 --> 01:21:57.579
Bud?

488
01:21:58.622 --> 01:22:00.916
They have her mother!

489
01:22:05.546 --> 01:22:07.172
Bud's its child?

490
01:22:15.806 --> 01:22:17.391
What's the plan?

491
01:22:17.474 --> 01:22:19.518
You free the Kalisk.

492
01:22:19.601 --> 01:22:21.228
I get my trophy.

493
01:22:29.361 --> 01:22:31.822
You have 20 minutes
to initiate launch.

494
01:22:32.698 --> 01:22:33.949
Let's go hunt.

495
01:22:41.123 --> 01:22:42.499
Wait here.

496
01:22:44.960 --> 01:22:47.629
You roll in there.
you're not exactly gonna fit in.

497
01:22:49.882 --> 01:22:51.216
I have an idea.

498
01:22:57.723 --> 01:22:59.266
<i>I see him. On me.</i>

499
01:25:32.336 --> 01:25:33.420
What are you doing?

500
01:25:41.553 --> 01:25:42.679
What are you doing here?

501
01:25:42.763 --> 01:25:44.306
I told you to get to the Yautja.

502
01:25:45.265 --> 01:25:48.185
You said to prepare the ship
for take off in 20 minutes.

503
01:25:49.311 --> 01:25:52.314
Then what are you doing here?
I gave you an order.

504
01:26:00.572 --> 01:26:02.532
What should we do about the creature?

505
01:26:03.659 --> 01:26:05.327
What creature?

506
01:26:10.582 --> 01:26:11.625
You should listen to her.

507
01:26:12.751 --> 01:26:15.671
- I should listen to her?
- I don't know.

508
01:26:19.508 --> 01:26:20.759
We need his eyes.

509
01:27:11.017 --> 01:27:14.020
Hi. Dek. How does it feel to be hunted?

510
01:27:16.231 --> 01:27:18.316
You tell me.

511
01:29:03.171 --> 01:29:04.756
This is the plan. yeah?

512
01:31:48.503 --> 01:31:49.671
Tessa.

513
01:32:19.784 --> 01:32:24.497
Betrayed by my own... sister.

514
01:32:50.732 --> 01:32:52.776
We are not sisters.

515
01:33:07.874 --> 01:33:10.126
That's not yours.

516
01:33:40.031 --> 01:33:41.866
Dek of the Yautja.

517
01:33:43.576 --> 01:33:46.246
Not yet.

518
01:34:39.007 --> 01:34:41.217
You've come here for revenge?

519
01:34:42.051 --> 01:34:44.888
I've come for my cloak.

520
01:34:48.933 --> 01:34:50.727
What is this?

521
01:34:50.810 --> 01:34:54.022
I've completed my hunt.

522
01:34:54.522 --> 01:34:56.900
That is my trophy.

523
01:34:58.151 --> 01:34:59.819
You disgrace our clan...

524
01:34:59.903 --> 01:35:01.321
And so did Kwei.

525
01:35:04.449 --> 01:35:08.077
Get rid of him.

526
01:37:02.150 --> 01:37:06.779
Perhaps the right son
did survive.

527
01:37:07.530 --> 01:37:09.782
Yield now...

528
01:37:09.866 --> 01:37:13.119
and take your place in our clan.

529
01:37:14.871 --> 01:37:18.041
I have my own clan.

530
01:37:46.110 --> 01:37:47.737
Finally earned that cloak.

531
01:37:54.619 --> 01:37:57.038
Dek of the Yautja.

532
01:38:34.784 --> 01:38:36.828
More friends of yours?

533
01:38:36.911 --> 01:38:38.663
No.

534
01:38:42.458 --> 01:38:44.335
It's my mother.

